-- Euro zone inflation pressures easing: ECB's Weidmann
-- 
-- Tue Mar 12, 2013 7:12am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/03/12/us-ecb-weidmann-inflation-idUSBRE92B0E720130312

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - Inflation pressures are easing in the euro zone and price expectations are firmly anchored, European Central Bank policymaker Jens Weidmann said on Tuesday. 
 "Inflation pressure is easing," Weidmann told a news conference after presenting the German Bundesbank's 2012 results. (Reporting by  Eva Kuehnen  and  Paul Carrel )